    <h4 style="font-size: 30px;font-style:unset;">MY NOTES</h4>
    <p style="font-size: 25px;text-align: left;"> The Murder:
        The story begins with the discovery of a murder: a man named Togashi is found dead in his apartment. The narrative introduces us to the protagonist, Ishigami, a brilliant but reclusive mathematician who lives next door to the murder scene.<br><br>The Investigation Begins:
        Detective Kusanagi and his partner, Detective Yukawa (who is an old acquaintance of Ishigami), begin their investigation. They focus on the murder victim's relationship with his ex-wife and her daughter, who have been living in the same building.<br><br> The Suspect:
        Yasuko Hanaoka, Togashi’s ex-wife, becomes a prime suspect after it is revealed that she had a confrontation with him prior to his death. The detectives begin to piece together the events leading to the murder.<br><br> The Mathematics of Crime:
        Ishigami, who has an unrequited love for Yasuko, quietly observes the investigation. He uses his mathematical skills to devise a plan to protect her, showcasing his intelligence and his deep affection for her.<br><br>The Alibi:
        Yasuko tries to create an alibi with the help of Ishigami. They concoct a story to mislead the detectives, demonstrating the lengths to which they are willing to go to cover up the crime.<br><br>The Discovery:
        As Kusanagi and Yukawa delve deeper, they uncover inconsistencies in Yasuko’s story. They begin to suspect that there is more to Ishigami than meets the eye, hinting at his potential involvement in the cover-up.<br><br>The Conflict:
        The tension rises as the detectives confront Yasuko, and the stakes become higher. Ishigami’s determination to protect Yasuko leads him to take increasingly drastic measures.<br><br>Love and Conflict:
